   =20
 =20
Hedge funds wage pandemic battle for top traders. WeWork to Restate Results=
 Due to Classification Error With Its SPAC Acquirer. Didi, Pinduoduo and Ot=
hers Could Seek Homecoming on U.S.  Delisting Threat.=C2=A0Capital One Is L=
atest Bank to Ditch Overdraft Fees. U.S.  Seeks Break for Swiss Trader Who =
Made $70 Million Illegally.=C2=A0Racy Affair Saga Between Jeff Bezos and En=
quirer Reaches Final Chapter.=C2=A0'Home Alone' house available for rent on=
 Airbnb.If you'd like to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form=
, right in your inbox, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subsc=
ribe to Money Stuff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] =
To be clear, one thing=C2=A0that never happened in my time at Goldman was L=
loyd Blankfein addressing me by name.[2] I cannot stress enough how fancifu=
l all of this dialogue is; the number of times that I had a good trade goin=
g that I would be excited to discuss with senior management was somewhere b=
etween zero and one.[3] DWAC has 28.75 million public shares outstanding, w=
hile the TMTG shareholders are getting 85.8 million shares in the merger pl=
us an additional 40 million possible earnout shares (see  footnote 11 here)=
. Crediting them with all of the earnout shares =E2=80=94=C2=A0not a sure t=
hing anymore =E2=80=94=C2=A0that gives Trump et al. 125.8 million shares of=
 the combined company and the public shareholders 28.75 million, or about 1=
8.6%. Crediting them with none of the earnout shares =E2=80=94=C2=A0as will=
 happen if the stock trades around $10 after the merger =E2=80=94=C2=A0then=
 Trump gets 85.8 million shares and the public has 25.1%.[4] To be clear, a=
 PIPE is a =E2=80=9Cprivate investment in public equity,=E2=80=9D meaning t=
hat it has to be an investment in the *public* company, the combined DWAC/T=
MTG at the time of their merger. It might be tempting for TMTG to go try to=
 raise a billion dollars *now*, in pure private investments, but that seems=
 like a terrible deal for the investors. The point of investing in the PIPE=
 is that you get public shares that you can then sell to someone else at th=
e market price.
